                                <title type="desc">Prologue to Sermo Angelicus</title>
                                <rubric>Prologus in sermone angelico de excellencia virginis</rubric>
                                <incipit>Cum beata byrgitta principissa nericie de regno swecie per plures annos habitaret in Roma</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="unknown">Qui viuit et regnat perhenniter cum eadem in secula seculorum</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Explicit prologus de sermone angelico</finalRubric>
                                <note>The prologue ends at the top of <locus from="61va" to="61va" scheme="folios"/>, after which follows the rubrics for the readings for the Matins and the rubric for the Sermo Angelicus itself, but not the text.</note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107127">Eklund (1972)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="75" to="79" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="62ra" to="85rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Cantus sororum</title>
                                <rubric>Incipiunt hore que cantantur per sorores in monasterio sanctarum marie et byrgitte in wazsteno In dominica Inuitatorium </rubric>
                                <incipit>Trinum deum et vnum pronis mentibus adoremus Virginique matri gratulantibus animis iugiter iubilemus.</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="unknown">Sancta maria mater domini nostri ihesu christi ... Benedicamus in laudem patris qui matrem suam mariam et cetera.</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="84vb" to="85ra" scheme="folios"/>: Benedicamus-versicles. Variants with Alleluia. <quote xml:lang="la">In dominica istud Benedicamus virginis filio <gap reason="editorial"/> Sabbato istud Benedicamus domino<gap reason="editorial"/> digna tali priuilegio alleluia alleluia alleluia</quote>. <locus from="85rb" to="85rb" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle: <quote xml:lang="la">Ymnus in festiuis beate marie virginis</quote>.</note>
